name: Strength Endurance w/20sec #2
description:
You are focussing on Strength Endurance work by completing steady, low cadence intervals. Strength Endurance increases crank torque and therefore recruits more of your fast-twitch muscle fibres. After warming up and completing a period of endurance 'free-riding', you will complete 3 x 8min min Strength Endurance intervals. However, each SE effort is finished off with a 20sec high cadence effort. Take note of the target cadence throughout the session.
